    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>We All Scream for Ice Cream!</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20100204.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <b>Thursday, February  4, 2010</b> &mdash;
    On a recent evening at the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=5">Downtown Entertainment Complex</a>, moviegoers and <a href="http://millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=520">Arcade</a> gamers were stopped in their tracks by a giant ice cream cone. Unfortunately, it wasn&#039;t edible. But what was edible was the sprawling selection of delicious goodness waiting just inside the new store beside it!<br><br>That&#039;s right: In case you haven&#039;t noticed, an <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=5">Ice Cream parlor</a> has taken over the old Snack Shop, in honor of the NEW ice cream-flavored Fruit Roll-Ups&reg; Scoops&trade;! Each yummy roll comes in three delectable, fruity ice cream flavors&mdash;and feature tongue tattoos in the shape of cones. Talk about lots of fun rolled into one super snack! Apparently, Mayor Wright found the orange-strawberry-raspberry combos so irresistible that he was inspired to open the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=5">Ice Cream Shop</a> and launch a new <a href="http://millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=520">Ice Cream Memory Game</a> to celebrate their arrival!<br>
<br>
Wright himself told us, &quot;As an avid moviegoer, my sweet tooth gets the best of me&mdash;and ice cream is the perfect companion for a flick. Plus, it was time for something new. But don&#039;t worry! You can still find your favorite hot dogs, smoothies, and other Snack Shop goodies at the <a href="http://dev.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=4&sortby=46&scrollside=left">Grocery Store</a>.&quot;<br><br>This said, you&#039;ll be surprised at the variety of cool stuff sold inside. Keith Umai, Millsberry Museum curator, was among the excited onlookers. [url=<a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=5">]&quot;Banana split sundaes; raspberry, orange, and strawberry ice cream cones; ice-cream scoop chairs and other ice cream-themed items; and of course, Fruit Roll-Ups&reg; Scoops&trade;</a> are among the many offerings you&#039;ve got to check out for yourself!&quot;<br><br><br>The curator also promised we weren&#039;t the first passersby to be surprised, noting &quot;When I saw a giant ice cream cone on top of the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=5">Entertainment Complex</a>, I thought I was seeing things. Soon, though, I realized my dream had come true! An ice cream store had finally landed in Millsberry!&quot;<br><br>&quot;To me,&quot; Keith explained, &quot;ice cream can be a work of art, just like the paintings hanging all around me at the museum. For instance brightly colored ice creams, all swirled together with different toppings, are a delight to behold. And Fruit Roll-Ups&reg; Scoops&trade; are also lots of fun. You can eat each flavor by itself by pulling them apart&mdash;or you can eat &#039;em all rolled up, for a fruity-sweet treat. Plus, you never know...you just might get a tongue tattoo of an ice cream cone on your tongue!&quot;<br><br>Actually, we figure some Millsberrians already have tongue tattoos, given the crazy popularity of the new <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=5">shop</a>. And right next door at the <a href="http://millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=520">Arcade</a>, people are lining up to play the new <a href="http://millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=520">Ice Cream Memory Game</a>. Simply flip over the cards two at a time and try to find a match before time runs out. (Matches include pictures of ice cream cones and other inviting images.) We can&#039;t wait to see who gets on the Top Scorer&#039;s Board&mdash;though our best guess is Mayor Wright who, as mentioned earlier, helped design the game. Wright had no comment on our prediction, but he might&#039;ve kept mum just to hide his tongue tattoo!
    </div>

